headline.main: Anthony Eden Is Dead at 79; Anthony Eden: Although Typecast for Success, He Was Out of Step With History Career Built on Style and Dash Ended With Invasion of Egypt

snippet: LONDON, Jan. 14 Sir Anthony Eden, who won renown as Britain's Foreign Secretary for his stand against fascism in the 1930's but whose career as Prime Minister was wrecked by the Suez invasion of 1956, died in his sleep today at his home in Wiltshi...
